How To Create A New Fork and Clone a Repository.

Create a GitHub account via https://github.com/join. Download and install oXygen XML editor (https://www.oxygenxml.com/xml_editor/download_oxygenxml_editor.html). Note: A license key is required and can be obtained from the administrator. Download and install GitHub Desktop (https://desktop.github.com/). 

Accept invitations for the lim-data and the lim-site. 

Create a fork repository on GitHub website: The master repository is: https://github.com/sfu-dhil/lim-data. Log in to your ID and click on “Fork”. 
![image1](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.1.png)

Open GitHub Desktop.
![image2](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.2.png)

Click on “Clone a Repository from the Internet”. 
![image3](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.3.png)

Ensure that the page is refreshed. Then, click on your repository (eg. shaunajudith/lim-data), select a local path of your choice (eg. Desktop), and then click on “Clone”. 
![image4](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.4.png)

A pop up may appear asking “How are you planning to use this fork?”. Select “To contribute to the parent project” and click “Continue”. 
![image5](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.5.png)

Open Oxygen XML Editor. Click on “sample.xpr” and then “Open Project".
![image6](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.6.png)

Open the Lim-Data folder created earlier, select “lim.data.xpr” and click “Open”. A pop-up will ask you to confirm your selection, click “Yes”. 
![image7](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.7.png)

Go to the top panel, click on “Oxygen XML Editor” and select “Preferences”. 
![image8](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.8.png)

In the “Type filter text” box, type in the word “wrap”. Then, under “text”, check the box next to “Line wrap”.
![image9](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.9.png)

To create a New Contributor, right click on the “contributors” folder, and then select “New” and then “File”.
![image10](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.10.png)

Select the “templates” folder, and then click on “New Team Member/ Contributor Document”. Change the file names to the author’s initials (eg. SJI.xml).
![image11](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.11.png)

To edit a template, replace the green text (the XML Comment) with your text. For instance, edit the forename, surname and display name. 
![image12](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.12.png)

Workflow for saving changes: Click on the “Save” icon or press “Control+S”. Click on the “Validate” button. 
![image13](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.13.png)

Go to GitHub Desktop. At beginning of every work day: click on the “Fetch origin” button.
![image14](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.14.png)

Add a title and description of the changes you have made (for instance, change the title to “Updated Profile SJI.xml” and add an informal description). Then, select “Commit to main”. 
![image15](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.15.png)

In order to update the changes on GitHub, click on “Push Origin”. 
![image16](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.16.png)

To verify that the changes have been uploaded to GitHub, visit the website, and refresh the page. 
![image17](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.17.png)

When you are ready for the changes to be reflected on the website, you need to contribute to the main repository. Click on “contribute” and then “Open pull request”. 
![image18](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.18.png)

Review your changes and click on “Create pull request”. 
![image19](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.19.png)

A new window will open. Add a title and a comment to provide an update about the work. Click on “create a pull request” button to confirm. The administrator will review and accept this request. 
![image20](https://github.com/shaunajudith/lim-schema/blob/main/docs/images/1.20.png)
